7	//! Port of `prettyLNTerm`/`prettyTerm` from
8	//! `lib/term/src/Term/Term.hs` (lines 267-297) and the `Show LVar` /
9	//! `Show Name` instances from `lib/term/src/Term/LTerm.hs`.
10	//!
11	//! Produces the same surface syntax Tamarin's interactive UI uses:
12	//!
13	//! - AC operators render in infix form: `Mult` => `*`, `Xor` => `⊕`
14	//!   (the single character U+2295, matching the Haskell side's `\8853`),
15	//!   `Union` => `++`, `NatPlus` => `%+`.
16	//! - `pair`-trees flatten into `<a,b,c>` notation.
17	//! - `exp(a,b)` renders as `a^b`, `diff(a,b)` stays as `diff(a, b)`.
18	//! - The `%1` constant (`tone`) prints as `%1`.
19	//! - Constants print as `'name'` (matching Haskell's
20	//!   `Name PubName "alice"` => `'alice'`).
21	//! - Variables print as `~k`, `$pk`, `#i`, `%n`, etc., with `.idx`
22	//!   suffix when `idx > 0`.
23	//!
24	//! Two entry points are exposed:
25	//! - [`pretty_lnterm`] returns a `String` (port of `prettyLNTerm`).
26	//! - `impl Display for LNTerm` (technically on `Term<Lit<Name, LVar>>`).
27	
28	use std::fmt;
29	
30	use crate::function_symbols::{
31	    diff_sym, exp_sym, nat_one_sym, pair_sym, AcSym, CSym, FunSym, EMAP_SYM_STRING,
32	};
33	use crate::lterm::{sort_prefix, LSort, LVar, Name, NameTag};
34	use crate::term::Term;
35	use crate::vterm::Lit;
